title: Rugby World Cup: How the quarter-finals are shaping up
text:
Romania - Eliminated 
WHAT DOES IT MEAN? 
Italy's lack of fight in Pool D has left it as an easy two horse race for top spot in Pool D - which will be decided tomorrow morning when France take on Ireland at Millennium Stadium. The loser has to face the All Blacks, and neither team particularly fancies that prospect. 
Remaining Games 
Italy v Romania, Sandy Park 
France v Ireland, Millennium Stadium 
Quarter-finals outlook 
QF 1 - South Africa v Wales, Twickenham 
QF 2 - All Blacks v Ireland/France, Millennium Stadium 
- Winners to face off in semifinal 1 
October 19 
QF 3 - France/Ireland v Argentina, Millennium Stadium 
QF 4 - Australia v Scotland, Twickenham 
- Winners to face off in semifinal 2
